SIMPLE: thorny
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thorny
<hw>Thorn"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Thornier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Thorniest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧orniht</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of thorns or
spines; rough with thorns; spiny; <as>as, a <ex>thorny</ex> wood; a
<ex>thorny</ex> tree; a <ex>thorny</ex> crown</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Like a thorn or thorns; hence, figuratively,
troublesome; vexatious; harassing; perplexing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>thorny</xex> point of bare distress.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The steep and <qex>thorny</qex> way to heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Thorny rest-harrow</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd>rest-harrow.</cd> -- <col><b>Thorny trefoil</b></col>, <cd>a prickly
plant of the genus <gen>Fagonia</gen> (<spn>Fagonia Cretica</spn>,
etc.).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thoro</ent>⟦br⟧
